                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What is Zuxton Node?</h2>
                        <p>Zuxton is a modular node validator operating on The Open Network (TON) blockchain. It employs the Triangular Arbitrage Network method, combining blockchain, Cloud Computing, and Client Device Browsers into a unified decentralized application (DApp).</p>
                        <p class="mt-4">This design enables nodes to be validated every minute without overburdening the user's resources. The client side uses only 33% of the device's resources, ensuring a lightweight experience.</p>
                        <p class="mt-4">Zuxton implements Proof of Contribution (PoC) on the TON network, where user commitment as a network validator is recorded with a unique PoC secretKey. Each user receives a unique PoC secretKey that operates with varying algorithms during blockchain execution.</p>
                        <p class="mt-4">Additionally, Zuxton issues a reward token called ZTON on the TON network, distributed to users who successfully operate nodes on Zuxton.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">How to Operate a Node on Zuxton</h2>
                        <div class="space-y-6">
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">1. Install the TON Wallet</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>Download the Tonkeeper Wallet from the Play Store or App Store.</li>
                                    <li>Alternatively, use the Tonkeeper browser extension for Chrome.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">2. Set Up Your Wallet</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>Create a new wallet or import an existing wallet.</li>
                                    <li>Using an account with a transaction history is recommended.</li>
                                    <li>Alternatively, create two wallets in Tonkeeper and make small transactions between them.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">3. Prepare 1 TON + Gas Fee</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>To run a node, you'll need 1 TON + Gas Fee as proof of your commitment to the network (Proof of Contribution)—this is a one-time action.</li>
                                    <li>PoC prevents spam and ensures the validity of node validation data.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">4. Connect Your Wallet to Zuxton</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>Visit zuxton.com and click Connect Wallet on the homepage.</li>
                                    <li>A popup will appear—select Tonkeeper and scan the QR code using the Tonkeeper Wallet app.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">5. Activate Proof of Contribution (PoC)</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>On the Zuxton dashboard, locate the Proof of Contribution Status section.</li>
                                    <li>Click Sign PoC Contract and complete the transaction in your Tonkeeper Wallet.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">6. Run the Node</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>Click Run Node to start. Points will update every minute.</li>
                                    <li>Ensure your network remains stable, your browser stays open, and your wallet remains connected.</li>
                                    <li>Check your node regularly to ensure it operates continuously.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[#29A5F8] mb-2">7. Submit Your Data</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                                    <li>Click Submit Your Data in Social Media Section</li>
                                    <li>Submit your data like TON wallet Address you use for run node (copy from wallet), X username and telegram username.</li>
                                    <li>Make sure to follow zuxton official social media on X an telegram.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
