                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What Is the Zuxton Airdrop Program?</h2>
                        <p>Zuxton has allocated 20% (20,000,000 ZTON) of its total 100,000,000 token supply for the airdrop program. This allocation is distributed to users who meet the eligibility criteria and required points.</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
                            <li>Airdrop Allocation: 20% of the total supply for users who qualify.</li>
                            <li>Point Conversion Pool: Zuxton has set aside 40% of the supply for point conversion.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="mt-4">Users' collected points can be converted to ZTON tokens at a ratio of 1:100 during the Token Generation Event (TGE). After the airdrop program concludes, users can continue running nodes and converting their points into ZTON tokens.</p>
                        <p class="mt-4">Zuxton also includes a referral program, where the number of referrals can increase the ZTON token amount received during the TGE.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Multi-Account Flexibility</h2>
                        <p>Zuxton allows users to operate multiple accounts on the same device or network because the system already enforces PoC for nodes.</p>
                    </div>

